24 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 58-71-41 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 58-71-41. First-year Provisional licensees; limitations.
26 (a) Except as provided in this section, a first-year provisional licensee shall have the same
27 authority as other persons licensed as bail bondsmen or runners under this Article. Except as
28 provided in subsection (d) of this section, a first-year provisional licensee shall operate only
29 under the direct supervision of and from the official business address of a licensed supervising
30 bail bondsman bondsman, who shall be responsible for the direct supervision of the provisional
31 licensee, for the first 12 24 months of licensure. A first-year provisional licensee may only be
32 employed by or contract with one supervising bail bondsman.
33 (b) When a first-year provisional licensee has completed 12 24 months of supervision,
34 six of which shall be uninterrupted, the supervising bail bondsman shall give notice of that fact
35 to the Commissioner in writing. If the licensee will continue to be employed by or contract with
36 the supervising bail bondsman beyond the initial 12-month 24-month period, the supervising bail
37 bondsman shall continue to supervise and be responsible for the licensee's acts.
38 (c) If the employment of or contract with a first-year provisional licensee is terminated,
39 the supervising bail bondsman shall notify the Commissioner in writing and shall specify the
40 reason for the termination.
41 (d) If, after exercising due diligence, a first-year licensed bail bondsman provisional
42 licensee is unable to become employed by or to contract with a supervising bail bondsman, the
43 first-year licensed bail bondsman provisional licensee must submit to the Department a sworn
44 affidavit stating the relevant facts and circumstances regarding the first-year licensed bail
45 bondman's provisional licensee's inability to become employed by or contract with a supervising
46 bail bondsman. The Department shall review the affidavit and determine whether the first-year
47 licensed bail bondsman provisional licensee will be allowed to operate as an unsupervised bail
48 bondsman. A first-year licensed bail bondsman is prohibited from becoming a supervising bail
49 bondsman during the first two five years of licensure.
50 (e) Provided all other licensing requirements are met, an applicant for a bail bondsman
51 or runner's license who has previously been licensed with the Commissioner for a period of at
