1 least 18 consecutive months and who has been inactive or unlicensed for a period of not more
2 than three consecutive years shall not be deemed a new licensee for purposes of this section."
3 SECTION 2.(c) Article 71 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
4 adding a new section to read:
5 "§ 58-71-41.1. Requirements for supervising bail bondsmen.
6 (a) A bail bondsman who seeks to act as a supervising bail bondsman or to restore a
7 revoked supervising bail bondsman status shall meet all of the following requirements:
8 (1) Submit an application on a form approved by the Commissioner and pay a
9 two hundred dollar ($200.00) application fee.
10 (2) Have five years of uninterrupted experience as a licensed bail bondsman in
11 this State.
12 (3) Have not violated an order of the Commissioner or had adverse administrative
13 action taken against the bail bondsman's license pursuant to G.S. 58-71-80.
14 (4) The bail bondsman shall possess or demonstrate the competence, experience,
15 or integrity considered by the Commissioner to be necessary to serve as a
16 supervising bail bondsman.
17 (b) A supervising bail bondsman shall submit to the Commissioner, on a form prescribed
18 by the Commissioner, both of the following:
19 (1) No later than May 31 of each year, a renewal application on a form prescribed
20 by the Commissioner. Failure to comply with this subdivision shall result in
21 revocation of a bondsman's status as a supervising bail bondsman.
22 (2) No later than the fifth business day of each month, a record of each provisional
23 licensee supervised by the supervising bail bondsman.
24 (c) A supervising bail bondsman shall not:
25 (1) Charge a fee for supervising a provisional licensee.
26 (2) Supervise more than two provisional licensees at one time."
27 SECTION 2.(d) Any bail bondsman (i) acting as or seeking to act as a supervising
28 bail bondsman or (ii) seeking to restore a revoked supervising bail bondsman status shall submit
29 the application and fee required by G.S. 58-71-41.1, as enacted by this act, within 60 days of the
30 effective date of this act.
