32 PART III. CHANGES TO DISCIPLINARY STATUTE TO ALLOW FOR
33 ADMINISTRATIVE ACTION BASED ON THE COMMISSION OF CERTAIN
34 CRIMES; PROVISIONAL LICENSEE CONFORMING CHANGE
35 SECTION 3. G.S. 58-71-80 reads as rewritten:
36 "§ 58-71-80. Grounds for denial, suspension, probation, revocation, or nonrenewal of
37 licenses.
38 (a) The Commissioner may deny, place on probation, suspend, revoke, or refuse to renew
39 any license issued under this Article, in accordance with the provisions of Article 3A of Chapter
40 150B of the General Statutes, for any one or more of the following causes:
41 …
42 (6a) Violation of a statute or ordinance that results in injury or death.
43 …
44 (8a) When, in the judgment of the Commissioner, the licensee has used
45 unnecessary or excessive force in performing the functions, duties, and
46 powers under the license issued by the Commissioner.
47 …
48 (b) The Commissioner shall deny, revoke, or refuse to renew any license under this
49 Article if if (i) the applicant or licensee is or has ever been convicted of a felony.felony or (ii)
50 pursuant to the provisions of Article 3A of Chapter 150 of the General Statutes, the
