18 PART IV. CHANGE DUE DATE FOR CONTINUING EDUCATION REQUIREMENTS
19 AND RENEWAL APPLICATIONS
20 SECTION 4.(a) G.S. 58-71-71(b) reads as rewritten:
21 "(b) Each year by June 30 May 15 every licensee shall complete at least three hours of
22 continuing education as provided by an approved provider in subjects related to the duties and
23 responsibilities of a runner or bail bondsman. This continuing education shall not include a
24 written or oral examination. A person who receives his or her first license on or after January 1
25 of any year does not have to comply with this subsection until June 30 May 15 of the following
26 year."
27 SECTION 4.(b) G.S. 58-71-75(b) reads as rewritten:
28 "(b) Renewal Application. – In even-numbered years, a bail bondsman or runner seeking
29 to renew a license shall shall, by May 15, provide the Commissioner prior to the expiration date
30 of the bail bondsman's or runner's current license, all of the following:
31 …."
