33 PART V. PHYSICAL LOCATION FOR OFFICIAL BUSINESS ADDRESS
34 SECTION 5. G.S. 58-71-40 reads as rewritten:
35 "§ 58-71-40. Bail bondsmen and runners to be qualified and licensed; license applications
36 generally.
37 (a) No person shall act in the capacity of a professional bondsman, surety bondsman, or
38 runner or perform any of the functions, duties, or powers prescribed for professional bondsmen,
39 surety bondsmen, or runners under this Article unless that person is qualified and licensed under
40 this Article. No licensee shall participate in or solicit assistance in securing custody of a principal
41 by another not licensed under this Article. No license shall be issued under this Article except to
42 an individual natural person.
43 …
44 (f) A licensee shall have an official business address that is a physical location in the
45 State of North Carolina. Official business addresses shall reflect an established office separate
46 and apart from any residence or other business. The address required by this subsection shall be
47 provided to the Commissioner designating where required business records are maintained upon
48 examination pursuant to G.S. 58-71-170. The physical location used as the official business
49 address must comply with all local or municipal zoning ordinances and regulations. Use of a post
50 office box as an official business address is prohibited."
51
